  "output": "## Performance Analysis — Avelo (Swift/SwiftUI, no React in this codebase)\n\n### 1. N+1 query patterns\n\n**`VoucherService.swift:1164-1175`** — `loadAccounts(ids:)` does one `SELECT` per account id in a voucher draft (runs on every post/edit).\n```swift\nfor id in ids {\n    guard let account = try accountRepo.findById(id) else { throw AppError.notFound(\"Account\") }\n    out[id] = account\n}\n```\nFix: add `AccountRepository.findByIds(_:)` (mirror the existing `findByCodes`) with a single `WHERE id IN (...)`.\n\n**`VoucherService.swift:1079-1085`** — `markAccountsUsed` issues one `UPDATE` per distinct account on every post/edit/reverse/cancel, even though `AccountRepository.markUsedBatch(_:)` already exists and is used correctly in `postBatch` (line 192). The single-voucher paths just never call it.\n```swift\nfor line in lines where seen.insert(line.accountId).inserted {\n    try accountRepo.markUsed(line.accountId)   // → accountRepo.markUsedBatch(Array(seen))\n}\n```\n\n**`ReportRepository+ComplianceReports.swift:195-226`** — `stockValuation` calls `inventory.runningBalance(itemId:)` per item, replaying full movement history each time. `stockAgeing` a few lines below (line 232) already does this correctly as one grouped query with `item_id IN (...)` — copy that pattern.\n\n### 2. Redundant computations (SwiftUI's version of \"re-render churn\")\n\n**`VoucherEditViewModel.swift:301-320`** — `totalDebitPaise`/`totalCreditPaise` re-scan `lines` on every access with no memoization. `isBalanced`, `canPost`, and `doubleEntryTotals` each call them independently, plus 2-3 reads from the view body — **up to 6 full array scans per render**, on every keystroke.\n```swift\npublic var totalDebitPaise: Int64 { (try? CheckedMath.sum(lines.lazy.filter { $0.side == .debit }...)) ?? 0 }\n```\nFix: compute both totals once in a single pass, cache as `@Published private(set) var totals: (debit: Int64, credit: Int64)`, recompute only in `addLine`/`removeLine`/`updateLine`.\n\n**`DashboardView.swift:10-11`** — `@Bindable var vm = vm` at the top of `body` means any single `DashboardViewModel` field changing invalidates the *entire* dashboard (KPI cards, P&L table, trial-balance strip). Compounded by `DashboardViewModel.reload()` (lines 31-111) running ~10 DB queries + a per-month loop **synchronously on the main actor** — unlike `VouchersViewModel`/`AccountsViewModel`, which detach. Same synchronous-main-actor pattern in `GSTViewModel.reload()`, `ReportsViewModel.reload()`, `BankingViewModel`, `SettingsViewModel`.\nFix: wrap these `reload()`s in `Task.detached` like the other view models already do, and split `DashboardView` into subviews scoped to the specific `@Published` fields they read so unrelated sections don't re-render.\n\n**`GSTView.swift:74-77`** and **`VouchersView.swift:180`/`AccountsView.swift:171`** — date-picker/search `.onChange` fires a full DB reload on *every keystroke/nudge*, no debounce. `VoucherEditViewModel.scheduleAutosave()` already has an 800ms-debounce pattern (line 225) — reuse it.\n\n**`AccountPicker.swift:147-170`** — `sortedAccounts`/`filteredAccounts` are plain (unmemoized) computed properties. One `AccountPicker` per voucher line binds to the same `vm.accounts`, so editing one line's amount re-sorts/re-filters the account list for every other line's picker too.\n\n**`CommandPaletteSheet.swift:25-80`** — `allCommands` rebuilds a ~30-entry array (each holding a closure) from scratch on every keystroke/arrow-press. Make it `static let`.\n\n### 3. Caching opportunities\n\n**`VouchersViewModel.swift:108-110`** — `accountName(_:)` does `accounts.first(where:)`, called once per visible table row per render → O(rows × accounts).\n```swift\npublic func accountName(_ id: Account.ID) -> String {\n    accounts.first(where: { $0.id == id })?.name ?? id.uuidString.prefix(8) + \"…\"\n}\n```\nFix: build `[Account.ID: Account]` once when `accounts` loads, look up by dict.\n\n**`NewAccountSheet.swift:63`** — `GSTStateCode.table.sorted(...)` re-sorted inside `body` on every re-render of the whole form. Make it a `static let sortedStates` on `GSTStateCode`.\n\n**`ReportRepository.swift:249-273` / `AccountTreeCache.swift:58-67`** — for companies without a persisted FY-opening-balance row, `signedOpeningBalance` falls back to one `movementTotals` query *per account*, run both on tree-cache rebuild and on every balance-sheet render. Batch into a single query for the whole account list.\n\n**`ReportRepository+FinancialStatements.swift:7-31,120-142`** — `balanceSheet` and `profitAndLoss` each independently reload and rebuild the account-group tree. `DemoCompanySeeder.populateDemoData` calls both back-to-back on the same company — pass a shared, pre-fetched group tree instead of refetching per report.\n\n### 4. Memory leaks\n\nNone found. `KeyboardMonitor`, `KeyboardBridge`, `AveloApp` all use `[weak self]`/`weak var` correctly; `RootView` uses `.onReceive` (SwiftUI-managed lifecycle); no dangling `Timer.scheduledTimer` or strong `delegate` anywhere.\n\nOne minor inconsistency: **`AccountTreeCache.swift:88-90`** uses `Task { await reload() }` (strong `self` capture) while `reload()` itself uses `Task.detached { [weak self] ... }`. Not a cycle (short-lived), but inconsistent — align it.\n\n---\n\n**Priority order**: #1 the `totalDebitPaise`/`markAccountsUsed` fixes (hot path, every voucher post) → #2 debounce the `onChange` reloads (main-thread jank users will actually feel) → #3 `AccountRepository.findByIds` batch → rest are lower-traffic paths.\n\nSkipped: building this out as an Artifact/report doc — you asked for the analysis, not a deliverable file. Say so if you want it as a tracked doc instead.\n",
